      'dn.faq.h': 'Frequently asked questions',
      'dn.faq.q1': 'Is this legally valid?',
      'dn.faq.a1': 'Yes. Per ZEDEIDU and Article 53b of Notarial Law, digitally executed acts with KEP have same legal weight as paper. eIDAS Regulation EU 910/2014 guarantees recognition.',
      'dn.faq.q2': 'What do I need to start?',
      'dn.faq.a2': '(1) KEP from KIBS, Telekom, A1 or CAOS. (2) Physical ID. (3) Stable internet. (4) Camera and microphone. KEP price: 1,500-3,000 MKD.',
      'dn.faq.q3': 'How much does it cost online?',
      'dn.faq.a3': 'Same as physical visit: 100-250 MKD + 50 MKD stamp. No extra fees. Payment: card, bank, PayPal.',
      'dn.faq.q4': 'Which notaries accept the system?',
      'dn.faq.a4': 'Currently 87 of 167 active notaries (52%). M-S target: 100% by Q3 2026. Free training for all.',
      'dn.faq.q5': 'For diaspora abroad?',
      'dn.faq.a5': 'Yes! Via eIDAS, EU citizens can use their national digital ID. For US/CA/AU — additional one-time consular verification.',
      'dn.faq.q6': 'What if connection drops?',
      'dn.faq.a6': 'Session auto-resets. 24 hours to resume with same notary, no extra fee. All digital evidence in encrypted vault 7 years.',
